<br>
Aego<br>
Focus<br>
Divine Strength<br>
Riotous Health<br>
&lt;Appropriate Resist Buff&gt; (ie. boss mob AE, or Talisman of Epuration else - hurting for DR).<br>
Speed<br>
Cadeau of Flame<br>
Shield of Eight<br>
<br>
That's 8 buffs, all there is to it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Usually I'm grouped with an incredible bard that twists:<br>
<br>
Cantata<br>
Warsong of Vah'Shir<br>
McVaxious Rousing Rondo (DS)<br>
Psalm of Warmth (DS)<br>
<br>
This is 12 slots here...<br>
<br>
Add slots for:<br>
<br>
Celestial Elexir<br>
Horrifying Visage<br>
Runes<br>
<br>
And I get to 15 - I even left out Divine Intervention which I usually get for &quot;boss&quot; mobs (I just trash my resist buff, unless Zlexak hehe) - I rarely even use my primal warsword anymore because if it procs avatar I'm screwing over the clerics that cast CE on me hehe.<br>
<br>
Anyway, just analyze the encounter and figure out how many slots will AE effects use up (Dragon Roar, AE dot(s), single target spells) and work backwards from there - my list is prioritized in what buffs I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> need</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in top - always leave a slot open for CE and Runes. <p><big><center>
